      "content": "\"Gentlemen, look upon this vast, untamed expanse, and see not wilderness, but a canvas awaiting the brushstrokes of British progress. It is our sacred duty, a burden we willingly bear, to introduce the light of civilization to these scattered, primitive peoples. We bring order where there is only chaos, and enlightenment where there is only superstition. Let us proceed with resolve, for the destiny of these lands, and indeed, the world, rests upon our steadfast hand.\"",
      "source": "target",
